libmdr (0.6.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix errno when buffer is too small in mdr_buf_from_fd
  * OpenBSD unveil/pledge tweaks 
  * Don't return from spawnproc_init() after forking
  * logging
  * We now get a timeout on mdrd_recv, which will return ETIMEDOUT on
    errno when we didn't gather a full MDR within this time; for this to
    work properly, we need to pass an offset so mdrd_recv can resume where
    it left off
  * Refactor mdrd_recv() to use a handle instead of passing a whole bunch
    of parameters; this also let's it resume in case we couldn't read a full
    message in one call, such as if we hit a timeout. With the timeout we
    can now also run tasks in-between each message.
  * We no longer use unpack_bein and instead we simply reference the umdr_vec
    entry which remains in-scope thanks to the handle; one less memcpy()!
  * mdrd_beout() now instructs the next call of mdrd_recv() to free the last
    session if we sent a reply with MDRD_BEOUT_FCLOSE instead of freeing
    directly, which could cause issues if we tried to access session fields
    later.
  * We made mdr_buf_from_fd() more generic, with a more generalized mdr_fill()
    function.

 -- Pascal Lalonde <plalonde@overnet.ca>  Fri, 17 Apr 2026 10:23:26 -0400

